ğŸ”„ Load Balancer (HAProxy Cluster)
â€¢	Why: Balances incoming traffic between multiple web/application servers to ensure high availability and fault tolerance.
â€¢	Cluster Setup: Two HAProxy instances (active-passive) using keepalived or VRRP to share a virtual IP.
o	If the primary fails, the secondary takes over with zero disruption.
â€¢	Distribution Algorithm: Uses round-robin to distribute requests evenly among backend servers.
